The following are my findings for amino acid sequences produced by my gene finder based on the Salmonella DNA sequence. The separate amino acid sequences were identified using Protein Blast and are all 100% matches confirming the presence of salmonella. The sequences corresponded to proteins secreted by Salmonella enterica, including those responsible for the invasion of Salmonella, surface antigens, gene transfer, and secretion of proteins. These properties enable a Salmonella virus to invade a host cell, secrete proteins, and multiply, affecting the host and leading to the infamous Salmonella infection
